## Code Review
When asked to run a persona review, invoke it using the Skill tool: `skill: "persona-review"`. This is an installed plugin command that auto-detects the project stack and launches specialized sub-agent reviewers (Implementer, Reviewer, Tester, UI/UX Designer, Security Auditor, Project Manager).

The user can also invoke it directly by typing `/persona-review`.

Arguments (pass via `args`):
- `feature/branch-name` — review a specific branch (default: current branch)
- `--stack <stack>` — override stack detection (dotnet-desktop, dotnet-library, aspnet-web, nodejs-api, static-site, salesforce, python-tools)
- `--overlay scientific-computing` — add scientific computing criteria
- `--rotation 4` — compact rotation (4 personas instead of 6)

Example: `skill: "persona-review", args: "feature/my-branch --stack dotnet-desktop"`
